  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>wedges</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with the <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1693919985846-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1693919985846-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1693919985846-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1693919985846-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1693919985846-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the wedges are cooking, crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing with the side of a knife and discard the skin</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1693919989942-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1693919989942-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1693919989942-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1693919989942-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1693919989942-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped cherry tomatoes </strong>to a bowl with <strong>half </strong>the <strong>diced onion </strong>(save the rest for later!), <strong>chopped basil</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Mix everything together – this is your <strong>bruschetta mixture</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo</strong> with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) – this is your <strong>balsamic mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1693919994064-x200.jpg",
